{"author":{"id":"bf52274e4b8baa03d436abcc532c02b6a719b9a772a7e952e18fcc8627570e5f"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782086870,"nonce":"Q67RtwqrZ5wR8HPd1NOoE32ignc=","title":"Implement a \"Did you mean …?\" with unknown keys","message":"When a key is unknown, we should suggest similar keys with a \"Did you mean …?\". For example, consider the workflow below:\n```scheme\n(define echo-command\n  (command #:inputs (message #:type string)\n           #:run \"echo\" message\n           #:outputs (output-message #:type stdout)))\n\n(workflow ((message #:type string))\n  (echo-command #:message messag))\n```\nCompiling this workflow, ccwl errors out as follows:\n```\nfoo.scm:7:26: error: Step echo-command supplied with unknown key messag. Known keys at this step are (message).\n    6 | (workflow ((message #:type string))\n    7 |   (echo-command #:message messag))\n```\nWe should probably add a \"Did you mean …?\" like so:\n```\nfoo.scm:7:26: error: Step echo-command supplied with unknown key messag. Did you mean message? Known keys at this step are (message).\n    6 | (workflow ((message #:type string))\n    7 |   (echo-command #:message messag))\n```\nWe could find similar keys using Jaccard similarity.","files":null}]}